  "prompt": "What are the legal ramifications of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious criminal offense with significant legal consequences. Typically, penalties can include:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Potential federal or state prison time\n- Substantial monetary fines\n- Asset forfeiture\n\n2. Federal prosecution\n- Violations of statutes like the Bank Secrecy Act\n- Potential charges under RICO (Racketeer Influenced and Corrupt Organizations Act)\n\n3. Financial penalties\n- Fines that can range from thousands to millions of dollars\n- Potential civil penalties\n\n4. Professional consequences\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Debarment from certain industries\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n\n5. International implications\n- Potential extradition\n- Global financial sanctions\n\nThe specific consequences depend on the scale of the offense, amount of money involved, and individual circumstances.",
